<subSubSection pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="70.[151,1436,382,659]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,598,623]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Remarks.</emphasis>
The population in 
<collectingCountry box="[546,641,598,623]" name="Vietnam" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
differs from the original description of the species (
<bibRefCitation author="Chen" box="[1264,1394,598,623]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" refString="Chen, Y. (1946) On the terrestrial oligochaeta from Szechuan III. Contributions from the Biological Laboratory of the Science Society of China, Zoological Series, 16, 83 - 141." type="journal article" year="1946">Chen 1946</bibRefCitation>
) in smaller body size, fewer setae and in having spermathecal pores paired in 5/6/7/8 (
<bibRefCitation author="Thai" box="[1076,1196,634,659]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" refString="Thai, T. B. (1997) New data on leaf - crawlers Pheretima Kinberg, 1863 in Vietnam and a key to species of this group from the mainland of Asia. TAP CHI SINH HOC, 19 (3), 1 - 7." type="journal article" year="1997">Thai 1997</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
